76561198002264700,Recommended,223830,15232617,"Posted: 6 April, 2015",all,Ekkoe,"I'll try to make this simple for you.Liked the original X-COM: UFO Defense? Then get this game.Never played the original X-COM: UFO Defense, but enjoy turn-based strategic games like Chess, Jagged Alliance, etc.? Get this game.Liked X-COM: Enemy Unknown (2012) but felt it had flaws in terms of strategic depth? Then get this game.Liked X-COM: Enemy Uknown (2012), but thought it was too hard? Don't get this game.Thought X-COM: Enemy Uknown (2012) was too ugly? Don't get this game.You're looking a very fine turn-based strategy squad base assault with base construction elements. It's slow, even a little dry sometimes, but definitely atmospheric. You'll need some wits and a whole lot of patience, but damn is it rewarding.Especially recommended for those who liked the original X-COM, because it is basically the remake we hoped we'd get in 2012.It's easy to compare XCOM:EU to Xenonauts, but it's also a little unfair: EU tried to do something new and accessible, and actually delivered quite well. In fact the only real complaint I had with the game was that it had bad support from devs, but that's because it had a console release and those don't patch easily. Regardless, Xenonauts comes out on top easily compared to EU, simply due to the superior basic design which was, for the most part, copied from the original XCOM.Some significant changes from the original:- Interceptor battles are now a mini-game with significant depth. An auto-resolve mode exists, but it is now actually a fun and worthwhile strategic element of the game (well beyond rock/paper/scissors);- Troops can now easily be organized by class equipment sets;- Workshops aren't profitable! Money management is very tricky;- During combat, HUD/Interface changes allow for easier troop and time-unit management;- During combat, obstacles are calculated in an intuitive and accurate way (something that looks to use virtual voxels to calculate whether the line of fire is obstructed. Very effective!);- There are now shields, which have 80HP (compared to a soldier's average starting HP of around 50) and can be combined with a pistol or a stun-baton;Etc.Concluding, for those familiar with the original XCOM, this is an interesting alternative frmo one perspective, or a viable upgrade from another. Personally, I consider it the latter.I score it 8.5/10 and consider it one of the best games I've ever played, notwithstanding the fact that it doesn't have the virtue of originality. Nonetheless, its execution is extremely refined and it's gameplay is enormously interesting."
