76561197996972957,Not Recommended,223830,34039590,Posted: 5 August,all,sir Evans,"TL:DR;B-O-R-I-N-G!This game is tedious AF and full of broken mechanics and outstanding bugs that can mess you up. Also totally imbalanced.Review: 5/10, purchase on sale if you have nothing else to do. Can safely skip it.Sound: 7/10That is quite a good audio for an otherwise ♥♥♥♥♥♥ game here.Although there is something wrong with audio sliders and it is difficult to get the volume just right, I don't complain about sound effects.Graphics: 5/10Apart from old-school look, there are just way too few assets and asset variations in the game.There are even mods that add more portraits, which is nice.However no mod can make map randomized.And once you have seen an area for the first time, it will look exactly the same every other time.In otherwords - all the maps are the same. There might be some different maps for a given area, but if you roll in the same map, everything is in the same place.EVERYTHING.Shrubs, cars, tress, stones etc.Why there is no randomisation, like placing different cars here and there is totally beyond me.Gameplay: 2/10Let's start it with stating that I have played most of UFO games.Except some ♥♥♥♥♥♥ FPS, I did all the classics, Aftermath, Firaxis versions, even UFO A.I. (free remake).When you compare xenonauts to them, Xenonauts simply suck.Here is why:- no geoscape. Flat map that stutters when you move it around, visibly and annoyingly- imbalanced weapons and armors and vehicles- imbalanced research- imbalanced base construction- imbalanced item production- buggy cover- buggy AI- game breaking bugs like your soldiers suddently can't move- shooting and grenade throwing mechanics- idiotic concept of TUs- very poor morale on soldiers- parts of environment are not destructible- can't breach ufo hull- no unit training outside of the missionI will be honest with you.This is X-Com mechanics, messed up to annoy you.First, upkeep and production cost.In order to produce an item, say lowest armor, you have to pay money for production, build workshop (cost you money), pay upkeep costs for workshop, hire engineers (costs you money) pay montlhy salary to them.And when you try to sell the item, it sells at half production cost.Meaning you cannot make profit from anything you construct.I modded that out, halving construction costs and times and salaries, and upping sale costs a bit, but FFS is the vanilla so unrealistic and stacked against having fun from the game.Second, tactical part is so crappy, it is insulting.If you have played any ufo games or games like Fallout1/2/tactics, you do know the concept of Action Points.Here, there are time units. Any action that is not related to firing weapons takes defined amount of TUs (I have modded it down again), but SHOOTING YOUR GUN TAKES PERCENTAGE.What does it mean?Two soldiers, one with 50 TUs and other with 100 TUs, move 20 TU in one direction. You would expect that first will shoot once, but another will shoot many times.You are wrong.Firing LMG will cost 30 TUs for first soldier, but 60 TUs for a second one.Developers had tested and tried mechanics done many times before, instead their opted for this stupidity.I am virtually certain, that If I was fast enought to run extra ten meters in the same time as another guy, I would also be able to pull the trigger at least one extra time. Again, I had to lower that to make game playable.Apart from that accuracy and damage is atrocious. Aliens always need one or two hits to kill your soldiers, initially unarmored soldier is one hitter for an alien handgun, later on heavily armored soldier will be blasted off from plasma cannon. Armours don't reduce damage done - they have a chance to stop it completelly at the expense of armour HP, which are getting used as the damage is received. But there is no indicator your armour is down and next shot will kill your trooper.And accuracy always sucks. Pistols are fantastically unaccurate, missing from point blank range.And damage has 50% random element to it (+/-), meaning that even if you shoot you might not harm enemy.And then there is psionics and panic. Psionic attacks can reach your soldiers from anywhere on the map, regardless of distance and obstacles. Panic attacs can happen to your most experienced veterans, if they survive alien shots, they usually panic or bleed to death. Or panic and run away from your medics, and bleed to death.Third, and most important, game is tedious, frustrating and boring.You do not have alien infiltration turning some organisations against you. You do not have multiple landing missions (they happened very rarely for me), just aliens floating around and bombing countries lowering your approval and funding.Interesting thing is that you loose the game if 1/3 of the world stops funding you. I had to mod this to at least half, because I think it was silly.There is no soldiers training when idle. Menu is difficult to navigate sometimes. Research is boring and proffesor comments on your engineers (he calls people building plasma cannons monkeys, brutes and primitives; why this ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ angle in the game?) is pretty messed up.There are few races of aliens, there are many classes of aliens, but alien classes are not mentioned. I would love to have some entries in xenopedia, but apparently that was too much work.Also aliens are usually camping in the last room in downed ufos, ready to return reaction fire at your grunts.Technology is standard, with no fancy things to them: for example you meet small alien scout drones, but game never lets you build your own.Tanks etc have 2x hitpoints of your soldiers (seriously?) and die way too soon.Also, while you can recover wreck of a downed plane, you cannot fix your destroyed tank.All of the above and more adds up to the game that is completelly devoid of any charm.It's not challenging, it's just brutal.For example one might think that developing alien based technology would make countries interested in paying you trucks of cash just to boost their defences against invasion, instead you sell it at a loss.Many small things like that add up to big pile of♥♥♥♥♥♥that is really not worth playing.After over a 50h on veteran I am so bored by all this randomness, saving, reloading, etc etc that enough is enough.Verdict:Skip it. Really not worth the trouble."
