76561197985847473,Recommended,223830,13720746,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Prophet Profit,"Summary: High-quality clone of the original X-Com: Enemy Unknown (1994).Positive: Its X-Com with modern features draped in a nice Cold War setting. The geoscape and battlescape are here with almost nothing left out (see below).The writing is actually a standout, reading the research reports was a small joy. Everything is presented in a way that is plausible in a late '70s timeline. The conclusions the science teams come away with are believable works of good fiction. I would love to provide an excerpt for your enjoyment here, but its too good to potentially spoil anything. There is also a bit of humor with a minor rivalry between the science and engineering departments.Speaking of research, as the game progresses and the Xenonaut program continues it's scientific advance, the graphics of your base screens update with the newfound technology; its a nice touch. Non-Xenonaut friendly forces also gain some of the technology you discover over time; neat!The game is also moddable.Negative: A few bugs: nothing too major, but there was one glitch that locked the game. This error only happend once over a 50+ hour campaign. There are some graphical errors when minimizing the game. Further visual glitches when aliens throw grenades; sometimes doubling in size until the animation completes, or appearing to throw twice in succession.There is a type of combat that doesn't involve traditional weaponry that is notablely missing from the game. The aliens still have it, but unlike every other X-Com clone the human forces simply cannot gain it... ever. Personally, I would have preferred for this type of combat to be rebalanced rather than removed from the game. There are only two ways to fight back against this ""weapon"" and neither one is reliable.There are very few maps in the battlescape. You'll end up on the same slightly-altered variations endlessly. There is a popular mod that fixes this.The infamous ""95%-chance-to-hit-but-still-somehow-misses"" RNG is still alive and well here. The aliens also get to throw grenades in some situations in which you cannot (""100% block"").Smoke Grenages are heavily nerfed, almost to the point of being useless. They were too powerful in the original for sure, but here they only last three turns (at best) and only work against a few types of aliens.The geoscape UFO activity happens all at once instead of being spaced out. Basically, the aliens coordinate one big ""assault-of-the-week"" every few days without variation. It would have been better to keep the old style of individual missions rather than this approach; it feels too synthetic.Overall: 8/10, I can't remember the last time a game has kept me playing in one sitting as long as this one. I felt like a kid again playing this wonderful game. Great job developers! With mods this is a nine out of ten game."
