76561198036146868,Recommended,223830,20667628,"Posted: 21 January, 2016",all,fogogamergamer,"The alternative to XCOM: Enemy Unknown/Within, or vice versa. Xenonauts sticks closer to the original XCOM than the official reboot, which leads to some notable differences (amongst others). In all three games, you lead a section of infantry against an alien force that's superior both in quality and quantity. Unlike XCOM, though, your troops are actually a crack team of veterans recruited from around the world. That is, your privates can actually hit a target 10 metres away and not freak out when it looks at them funny afterwards. Also in keeping with the traditional game, the clock's been rolled back - but even further than the original, to the late 1970s. Yes, that's right: your soldiers are using M16s and M60s, and the Soviet Union still exists. Your equipment can be far better or far worse than in the ""official"" reboot as a result.In conclusion, the game is a very good compromise, nestled between XCOM:EU and XCOM:EW with the Long War mod installed. If you want an ""easy"" game with modern graphics and a minimal air war component, play XCOM:EW. For a surreal-bordering-on-pure-evil level of difficulty, go with Long War. For something that's in the happy medium between the two (or if you just want a nostalgia trip), pick up Xenonauts. Heck, pick up both successors if you want. One can be just as good as the other, depending on what you're looking for."
