76561198144125800,Recommended,223830,11819232,"Posted: 22 August, 2014",all,catweaselcrow,"A remake of the original TBS classic X-Com:UFO Defence from the 90s.If you played any of the original Microprose X-Coms and were disappointed with the Firaxis reboot's lack of depth, then Xenonauts will not disappoint.It plays very similar to the original X-COM with some extra polish as you'd expect 20 years later.My favourite aspect is that the game has been opened up to the modding community, and there are some great mods out there that vastly expand the tech trees, maps, equipment etc etc.If you aren't familiar with the original, the game is split into a strategy layer, where you intercept UFOs, build up your bases, equip your troops and aircraft, do research etc, and a turn-based squad combat layer where you investigate crashed and landed UFOs, alien bases, terror sites etc.You never have enough money to do everything you want, and the difficulty ramps up as the invasion progresses.The graphics may seem a bit antiquated, but it's all about the gameplay, and rolling out your strategy for defeating the alien invasion.The ambient music is excellent, and the hours fly by as you get immersed in the game.In my opinion, a must-buy for any fans of the original series, and recommended for any TBS fans."
