76561198144593917,Recommended,223830,18842577,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,mikesanerd,"Xenonauts does a great job of hitting that sweet spot where they've managed to significantly improve upon the original XCom games without losing the essential essence of them.They clean up and improve the UI substantially, giving you data you didn't have in the 90s like hit probabilities. They revamp and scrub the game's economy, eliminating some of the easier ways to get money, forcing you to rely much more on maintaining good relationships with world governments. They revamp the research tree, making the progression of technologies more sensible and less vulnerable to work-arounds. They tweak the combat system, adding new weapon and equipment types so that much more strategy has to go into your soldiers' layouts.Even with all these changes, this is the game I loved back in the day--or maybe better yet, it's the game I never even dreamed XCom could have been. Anyone who liked the original XCom should definitely try this game. Younger gamers who don't remember the original may find this game too challenging or not flashy enough, but strategy enthusiasts should give this game a try as well."
