,Recommended,223830,28678825,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,SlightEye,"The goodXenonauts atcheaves what it set out to do: To be a spiritual succsessor to the first Xcom game.It has improved in some aspects over the original Xcom:The aircraft combat is less random and more skill based with its up to 3 v 3 air battles where you actually get to controll          the positioning and weapon useage of your aircraft. As opposed to the original where it was mostly luck based wheter your interceptors hit and/or/did not get hit in an encounter.The art in the xenopedia/ufopedia is what I personally enjoied alot in both the original and Xenonauts.Combat shields are a great addition to the game.The modding scene is still active and people are givig their best to make the game better.The badFlatland!The geoscape is flat and radar ranges and distances make no geological sense because there is no consideration for map deformation. If you like globes you will not find any here.The ground combat sprites look plane, like they made some models in a 3d art program and animated them there. Then made a bunch of low resolution images of the models to make the art for the ground combat. The art there has no character at all unlike the original Xcom.Unlike the original Xcom you can not make your soldiers or aleans:Jump down from roofs.Throw anything besides granades and explosives.Wake up from being uncouncious.Get tired from running.Take kontroll of the minds of aleans or civilians.Get hit in specific body parts and and lose apropreat stats for being wounded.Difficult to make mods for:The game engine is at best a derelict wreck with no source. It reports no errors and just crashes when things go wrong. Wich makes finding bugs in your mods way more difficult than it has to be.Due  to the difficulitys in the games development the game is in numerous separate peaces of code that use different files for tha same things. For example the weapon stats in the xenopedia/ufopedia and inventory and ground combat calculations are all in different files. While making a new weapon for the game you have to mod all three of the files witch all have slightly different formats.ConclusionsA polished game it certainly is not. But for the price they are asking it has sertainly given me many houers of entertainmant. And many of its smaller flaws, exept the ones I mentioned, have been fixed by the modders. So if you are looking for something a bit more like the old Xcom yo might want to give this game a try. But if you are short on money you might want to save up for the seqel."
