,Recommended,223830,21340625,"Posted: 20 February, 2016",all,apollo,"Many many years ago i was a big fan of the first UFO:Enemy Unknown and its sequel Terror from the Deep. I loved these games and played them for weeks and months. Some time later i came across the inofficial ""sequels"", Aftermath, Afterlight and Aftershock...but didn´t get comfortable with them. The foot prints of their unequaled predecessor where too big. The graphics, the gameplay...it has not been what i want an UFO-title to be.The newly released XCOM and XCOM2 dont felt right for me too, so i gave the open sourced UFO:Alien Invasion (UFO:AI) a try but as well, thats not what i expected to seeBy accident i found Xenonauts on Steam and was very curious about it. After something about 6 hours of gameplay i only can recommend this title to anyone, who wants a modern version of the original series.For me, an UFO-title does not need to have fancy top-notch 3D graphics, its all about gameplay and story. And there, Xenonauts does very well. I feel comfortable from the first time the UI is started. The gameplay is very similar to the original series, geo- and battlescape usage is self explanatory and straight forward. You´ll get familiar with it within minutes. The graphics even add to the atmosphere, they are modernized but not for the sake of having the best 3d graphics out there...they just feel right the way they are.For a long time, Xenonauts is the first UFO-type game i´m playing that makes me sorry about every soldier i loose in a battle. Exactly that is what i wan´t a UFO-title to be. Great work!"
