,Recommended,223830,34795220,Posted: 7 September,all,Mordgier,"At release this game had a few issues - crippling bugs and horrible balance issues that went well past making the game challenging to tedious.Over 3 years later, this is now a solid, enjoyable and ultimately a good game.  Largely as a result of community contributions to the community branch.The developers realized that their game did not offer the best modding support and that they didn't quite have the resources to fix a game that untimely was never all that popular.  So they did something almost no other dev does - they shared the code with the community.The result is the community branch and a mod manager that not only fixes the bugs but improves game balance and further lets you easily install mods that allow you to fine tune your game.This is not X Com Enemy Unknown or X Com 2 - it's far harder, far more brutal and admittedly more frustrating. Yet the reward for enduring the often unfair gameplay is the sense of success and tremendously deep gameplay.Yes this game is hard, yes I suggest playing with numerous mods that tune the difficulty down, yes it's not pretty, and your soldiers will never become superheros like they do in the XCom of today. There are no 'super powers' like dodging shots or being a guaranteed a miss. You will always be at the mercy of RNG and you will lose your troops at all stages of the game rather than having them become vastly more powerful than the aliens.In short - give this game a shot, hit up the community to figure out which mods you want and what strategies to use to deal with the aliens as the game will not hold your hand and expect to reload often or fail often."
