76561198131229739,Recommended,223830,34819149,Posted: 8 September,all,=AGP=Front1erm4n,"It's quite like the original X-COM. The controls are easy to grasp, the gameplay is great and the progression is nicely paced.The strategic layer revolves around shooting down UFOs, deploying to ground battles and managing the direction of your forces. You have to build the bases and recruit the personel while also researching and building new toys to reduce the mortality rate amongst your soldiers.The air battles are pausable and can be easy or impossible depending on the choices for the loadout of your fighters.The tactical battles where you will spend the most of your time are turn-based with you starting in your drop ship and having to explore the map. Starting to play the game you will most probably lose soldiers but since at the start of the game you are vastly outclassed in terms of technology you will find tactics to mitigate those disadvantages.Your tactics on the ground will depend on the equipment you give your soldiers. Maybe you want several machine gunners supported by shotgun troopers? Or rather bombard them with hand grenades? It is up to you.I have really enjoyed my playthroughs and I am looking forward to Xenonauts 2."
